member.name: T:Microsoft.Dynamics.Retail.Diagnostics.CustomerContentAttribute
member.summary: This is the data, information and code that C1 admins, C1 users, and C2 users (if present) provide to, transfers in, stores in or process in the Microsoft online service or product.
member.example: Customer-owned/ provided secrets (passwords, certificates, encryption keys, storage keys, Bring Your Own Key). Customer generated blob or structured storage data. Inferences when Customer Content remains. Machine learning built models with data that is private/unique to a customer (e.g. tenant specific dictionaries). E-mail body or email attachment, Customer's CRM database(s), Customer's access tokens used for data acquisition, acquired private messages from social platforms (e.g. Twitter, Facebook), customer-input search queries used to obtain social media data (includes customer-input topic names and customer search configurations), customer imported data, custom code, extensible controls (e.g. X++, HTML).

member.name: T:Microsoft.Dynamics.Retail.Diagnostics.EndUserIdentifiableInformationAttribute
member.summary: Data that directly identifies or could be used to identify the authenticated C1 or C2 user of a Microsoft service. EUII does not contain C1 admin data. EUII does not extend to other personal information found in Customer Content (e.g. contact lists are Customer Content), contact lists are Customer Content).
member.example: User-specific IP address (IPv4) Interface ID (last 64 bits of IPv6 address) User Principal Name (joe@company.com) Local-part of e-mail address (joe@contoso.com) E-mail subject line User name or display name Office number Employee ID Address Book Data Location Information of a person (Including Lat/Long) User's machine Name SIP URI International Mobile Equipment Identifier (IMEI) or Integrated Circuit Card ID (ICCID) Inferences if EUII remains.
member.remarks: C1 admin data is Account Data. Data about unauthenticated C2 users is Customer Content.

member.name: T:Microsoft.Dynamics.Retail.Diagnostics.EndUserPseudonymousIdentifierAttribute
member.summary: An identifier created by Microsoft tied to the C1 or C2 user of a Microsoft service. When EUPI is combined with other information (such as a mapping table), it identifies the end user.
member.example: User GUIDs or PUIDs. Other common GUIDs that are EUPI include: machine IDs, device IDs. Session IDs. Salted hashed EUII, while Microsoft retains the salt. Encrypted EUII, which Microsoft retains the encryption key and can decrypt.
member.remarks: EUPI does not contain information uploaded or created by the customer (Customer Content or EUII).

member.name: T:Microsoft.Dynamics.Retail.Diagnostics.OrganizationIdentifiableInformationAttribute
member.summary: Data that can be used to identify a particular tenant/ Azure subscription/ deployment/ organization (generally config or usage data).

member.remarks: Not linkable to a user. Does not contain Customer Content. Organizational GUIDs and/or Tenant GUIDs are System Metadata unless combined with OII. When Organizational or Tenant GUIDs are combined with OII, the aggregate data is OII.
